1
00:00:13,105 --> 00:00:15,045
(Lee Jun Young)

2
00:00:20,185 --> 00:00:22,815
(Lee Ju Myoung)

3
00:00:28,825 --> 00:00:31,495
(Jeon Hye Jin, Jin Goo)

4
00:00:46,105 --> 00:00:49,075
(Reborn Rookie)

5
00:00:59,555 --> 00:01:02,425
(Chairwoman Kang Jae Gyeong)

6
00:01:14,565 --> 00:01:15,565
Father?

7
00:01:20,775 --> 00:01:22,205
You should be happy.

8
00:01:23,175 --> 00:01:25,715
Your dead father has come back from the grave.

9
00:02:00,285 --> 00:02:01,345
Team Leader Hwang?

10
00:02:05,085 --> 00:02:06,215
Am I drunk?

11
00:02:07,585 --> 00:02:09,425
I'm sure it was my father.

12
00:02:10,925 --> 00:02:11,925
Chairwoman.

13
00:02:12,995 --> 00:02:15,125
- Chairwoman? - What?

14
00:02:16,365 --> 00:02:17,735
Were you seeing things?

15
00:02:18,835 --> 00:02:21,805
I've been calling your name. You called me "Father."

16
00:02:23,305 --> 00:02:24,305
What are you talking about?

17
00:02:27,375 --> 00:02:28,545
Is Chairman Na behind this?

18
00:02:29,205 --> 00:02:31,715
Will he really not be satisfied until you're dead?

19
00:02:35,215 --> 00:02:36,915
I don't think he'll stop with me.

20
00:02:39,855 --> 00:02:41,285
His final target is...

21
00:02:43,925 --> 00:02:45,455
Chairwoman Kang Jae Gyeong.

22
00:02:47,095 --> 00:02:48,125
I figured.

23
00:02:49,025 --> 00:02:51,765
A cornered Chairman Na is capable of anything.

24
00:02:52,335 --> 00:02:53,335
No.

25
00:02:54,535 --> 00:02:55,765
Not Chairman Na.

26
00:02:59,735 --> 00:03:00,945
My target.

27
00:03:04,045 --> 00:03:05,075
What are you talking about?

28
00:03:07,915 --> 00:03:08,915
Don't tell me...

29
00:03:14,525 --> 00:03:16,355
Was this all your doing, Team Leader Hwang?

30
00:03:16,555 --> 00:03:18,325
Do you mean how I exposed Na Eun Se's atrocities...

31
00:03:18,395 --> 00:03:20,255
and stopped you from taking over Taeyang Energy?

32
00:03:21,725 --> 00:03:24,035
Or how I made you lose Chairman Na's slush fund?

33
00:03:25,065 --> 00:03:26,934
- Hwang Jun Hyeon. - But you managed...

34
00:03:26,935 --> 00:03:28,165
to protect Choiseong Group,

35
00:03:29,365 --> 00:03:31,735
and you found out who really killed your father,

36
00:03:33,105 --> 00:03:35,045
so you've gotten all the revenge you wanted, right?

37
00:03:36,705 --> 00:03:39,275
Then may I tell you what I want now?

38
00:03:47,585 --> 00:03:48,625
(Corporate Check)

39
00:03:50,525 --> 00:03:52,625
(Give me Choiseong.)

40
00:03:55,625 --> 00:03:56,895
What do you think you're doing?

41
00:03:57,195 --> 00:03:59,535
I'm here to be compensated for the life you ruined.

42
00:04:02,035 --> 00:04:03,265
And for the record,

43
00:04:05,905 --> 00:04:07,105
I don't compromise.

44
00:04:32,235 --> 00:04:33,235
So?

45
00:04:33,495 --> 00:04:36,035
How did it feel facing Kang Jae Gyeong?

46
00:04:37,605 --> 00:04:38,605
Gosh.

47
00:04:39,575 --> 00:04:40,975
I was scared to death,

48
00:04:41,705 --> 00:04:43,375
but I think it went well somehow.

49
00:04:44,415 --> 00:04:46,215
And I said everything you told me to.

50
00:04:52,115 --> 00:04:54,785
Give Kang Yong Ho my regards.

51
00:04:59,955 --> 00:05:00,965
Father.

52
00:05:10,735 --> 00:05:11,735
Father.

53
00:05:12,935 --> 00:05:14,275
Father, are you with us?

54
00:05:23,955 --> 00:05:26,585
Where am I?

55
00:05:30,695 --> 00:05:33,355
I'm alive...

56
00:05:36,025 --> 00:05:37,025
Father.

57
00:05:37,535 --> 00:05:39,935
You were pronounced dead, but you suddenly started breathing.

58
00:05:40,295 --> 00:05:42,205
Jae Seong and I brought you here,

59
00:05:42,365 --> 00:05:45,375
but since you were unconscious, we didn't tell anyone.

60
00:05:45,835 --> 00:05:47,205
You've only just woken up.

61
00:05:48,145 --> 00:05:51,275
Give Kang Yong Ho my regards.

62
00:05:54,615 --> 00:05:55,615
That punk...

63
00:05:57,185 --> 00:05:59,055
He's in danger.

64
00:05:59,615 --> 00:06:01,525
No, Father. Not yet.

65
00:06:01,725 --> 00:06:04,555
You just woke up after months. You need to rest...

66
00:06:08,725 --> 00:06:10,025
There's no time.

67
00:06:10,565 --> 00:06:12,695
Chairman Na is trying to kill Hwang Jun Hyeon.

68
00:06:13,035 --> 00:06:14,535
We have to find him, no matter what.

69
00:06:15,835 --> 00:06:16,865
You can't, Father.

70
00:06:17,175 --> 00:06:20,845
- You could get seriously hurt. - I've already died once.

71
00:06:25,815 --> 00:06:26,815
Father.

72
00:06:29,945 --> 00:06:32,215
- Who is this? - It's me.

73
00:06:32,955 --> 00:06:34,055
Sang Jae.

74
00:06:37,995 --> 00:06:40,455
Is it really you, Chairman?

75
00:06:42,765 --> 00:06:43,765
But...

76
00:06:44,495 --> 00:06:47,535
does that mean Hwang Jun Hyeon is alive?

77
00:06:48,905 --> 00:06:50,405
We're heading toward Yeongjong Island, sir.

78
00:06:50,805 --> 00:06:52,275
It looks like Chairman Na really took him.

79
00:06:52,405 --> 00:06:53,475
Secretary Nam, get all your contacts...

80
00:06:53,535 --> 00:06:54,805
in the prosecution and police on the line.

81
00:06:54,905 --> 00:06:56,445
If they don't want to be all over the news...

82
00:06:56,505 --> 00:06:57,975
with Na Byeong Mo, the man they let go,

83
00:06:58,145 --> 00:06:59,245
tell them to arrest him right now.

84
00:07:01,115 --> 00:07:02,645
(International Call)

85
00:07:09,755 --> 00:07:10,755
Honey.

86
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:13,125
It's me.

87
00:07:28,875 --> 00:07:29,945
This time,

88
00:07:31,375 --> 00:07:33,345
I'll never let him die.

89
00:07:43,025 --> 00:07:44,794
He's heavier than he looks.

90
00:07:44,795 --> 00:07:46,195
Hey, the chairman's leaving.

91
00:07:46,295 --> 00:07:47,995
- Get in. - Yes, sir.

92
00:08:12,655 --> 00:08:13,955
Get rid of him.

93
00:08:14,525 --> 00:08:16,955
- So he can't be recycled. - Yes, Chairman.

94
00:08:17,355 --> 00:08:18,355
Let's go.

95
00:08:20,695 --> 00:08:21,795
Finish the job and get back.

96
00:08:57,565 --> 00:08:58,565
Go after him!

97
00:08:59,365 --> 00:09:00,395
Get him now!

98
00:09:35,665 --> 00:09:36,905
Hey, block the other side. Quick.

99
00:10:02,695 --> 00:10:04,695
- What do you think you're doing? - Get out!

100
00:10:04,765 --> 00:10:05,835
All right!

101
00:10:07,935 --> 00:10:10,135
Thankfully, President Kang Jae Seong acted quickly.

102
00:10:11,075 --> 00:10:12,175
Where is he?

103
00:10:13,535 --> 00:10:15,445
- Hwang Jun Hyeon! - They found him.

104
00:10:17,345 --> 00:10:19,375
- What? - He'll be okay.

105
00:10:20,815 --> 00:10:21,815
Who?

106
00:11:18,905 --> 00:11:21,305
Where are you going in your condition?

107
00:11:23,175 --> 00:11:25,345
How on earth did you survive?

108
00:11:27,345 --> 00:11:29,245
Because it would be too unfair to die like this.

109
00:11:31,415 --> 00:11:33,485
I haven't even received a proper apology yet.

110
00:11:36,525 --> 00:11:37,625
I'm sorry.

111
00:11:38,155 --> 00:11:39,255
I'm sorry.

112
00:11:41,095 --> 00:11:42,565
It's all my fault.

113
00:11:43,395 --> 00:11:44,395
It seems so.

114
00:11:44,935 --> 00:11:46,935
Why are all your children like that?

115
00:11:47,135 --> 00:11:50,065
Do you know how many times I almost died in your body?

116
00:11:51,375 --> 00:11:54,175
You acted so high and mighty and talked down to me,

117
00:11:54,775 --> 00:11:56,875
but it turns out your life isn't that great after all.

118
00:11:57,745 --> 00:11:59,945
It's as if everyone thinks they have to kill you to survive.

119
00:12:01,545 --> 00:12:02,615
No way.

120
00:12:06,455 --> 00:12:08,955
Do you have all the memories from when you were in a coma?

121
00:12:11,025 --> 00:12:12,655
I know for certain that Kang Jae Gyeong...

122
00:12:12,725 --> 00:12:14,725
and Kang Jae Seong were behind the hit-and-run.

123
00:12:16,195 --> 00:12:17,225
Those two...

124
00:12:18,165 --> 00:12:20,335
I have to see them get the punishment they deserve.

125
00:12:23,965 --> 00:12:25,035
Of course.

126
00:12:27,335 --> 00:12:29,375
Can you do as I say?

127
00:12:31,315 --> 00:12:34,015
I've set many things in motion using your body.

128
00:12:37,285 --> 00:12:38,715
And how can I trust you?

129
00:12:40,715 --> 00:12:43,224
You'll just cover for your children and get swayed again. It's obvious.

130
00:12:43,225 --> 00:12:45,455
That will never happen.

131
00:12:47,925 --> 00:12:50,065
The plan to catch Kang Jae Gyeong...

132
00:12:53,065 --> 00:12:54,135
is already in place.

133
00:13:04,475 --> 00:13:06,075
But what about the camera?

134
00:13:06,645 --> 00:13:08,015
You must have been caught on it.

135
00:13:08,315 --> 00:13:09,345
Don't worry.

136
00:13:10,085 --> 00:13:12,785
My friend, Lee Sang Jae, will take care of it.

137
00:13:14,525 --> 00:13:15,885
So you do have one good person around you.

138
00:13:16,555 --> 00:13:19,195
I thought you were only surrounded by people who use you.

139
00:13:19,395 --> 00:13:22,065
You punk. You haven't changed a bit.

140
00:13:22,465 --> 00:13:23,765
Always speaking the truth.

141
00:13:24,995 --> 00:13:26,165
Oh, well.

142
00:13:26,595 --> 00:13:29,405
I'm the one who raised my children to be a merchant...

143
00:13:29,465 --> 00:13:31,575
who'd sell out their own dead father.

144
00:13:32,275 --> 00:13:33,805
Who can I blame?

145
00:13:34,675 --> 00:13:36,805
Not all of your children are like that.

146
00:13:40,375 --> 00:13:41,745
Your youngest daughter.

147
00:13:43,145 --> 00:13:44,855
Kang Bang Geul is a good person.

148
00:13:48,655 --> 00:13:50,125
How do you know my Bang Geul?

149
00:13:53,995 --> 00:13:55,965
Fasten your seatbelt. We're leaving.

150
00:13:57,395 --> 00:13:59,565
(Incoming Call, Extension 101)

151
00:14:00,295 --> 00:14:02,435
- This is the Security Team. - What about the CCTV footage?

152
00:14:02,605 --> 00:14:05,035
There was a system error, so it stopped working for a moment.

153
00:14:05,605 --> 00:14:08,145
The power outage was likely caused by that as well.

154
00:14:13,475 --> 00:14:15,245
I'm sure that was Father.

155
00:14:18,085 --> 00:14:19,115
Na Byeong Mo.

156
00:14:19,415 --> 00:14:20,855
You're under arrest for the kidnapping...

157
00:14:20,915 --> 00:14:22,055
and assault of Hwang Jun Hyeon.

158
00:14:22,555 --> 00:14:24,225
This is all a useless charade.

159
00:14:24,525 --> 00:14:27,255
Go on, lock me up. I'll get out again, so just try it.

160
00:14:28,725 --> 00:14:30,725
Stop before you embarrass yourself even more.

161
00:14:31,465 --> 00:14:33,295
Those connections you're counting on...

162
00:14:33,765 --> 00:14:36,605
- have already been severed. - Why you little... "You"?

163
00:14:38,805 --> 00:14:40,635
Your daughter contacted me.

164
00:14:41,845 --> 00:14:43,375
She said she only did what her father told her to...

165
00:14:43,445 --> 00:14:44,675
and that she's going to turn herself in.

166
00:14:45,375 --> 00:14:47,575
No. That can't be.

167
00:14:47,685 --> 00:14:50,215
My daughter would never say something that stupid.

168
00:14:50,745 --> 00:14:52,255
You think this is over?

169
00:14:52,555 --> 00:14:55,825
I'm Na Byeong Mo. You hear me?

170
00:14:59,255 --> 00:15:01,095
(Villa Team)

171
00:15:02,425 --> 00:15:04,795
- Is something wrong? - It's me, Jae Seong.

172
00:15:05,335 --> 00:15:06,435
Your father woke up.

173
00:15:06,735 --> 00:15:09,235
- I'm on my way. - He's not here.

174
00:15:10,935 --> 00:15:12,135
Then where is he?

175
00:15:15,775 --> 00:15:17,375
Mr. Lee, I'm here.

176
00:15:17,845 --> 00:15:20,475
But is Hwang Jun Hyeon really coming here?

177
00:15:20,845 --> 00:15:22,315
Yes, he's almost there.

178
00:15:22,845 --> 00:15:25,255
You were able to reach him? He won't answer any of my calls.

179
00:15:26,985 --> 00:15:28,485
You're hiding something, aren't you?

180
00:15:31,755 --> 00:15:32,925
Excuse me.

181
00:15:34,865 --> 00:15:36,295
Hey, Hwang Jun Hyeon!

182
00:15:42,705 --> 00:15:45,075
Is this why you told me to stay out of it?

183
00:15:45,705 --> 00:15:48,805
I thought you were going to die. That I'd never see you again.

184
00:15:48,845 --> 00:15:50,805
Do you have any idea how worried I was?

185
00:15:52,615 --> 00:15:53,715
Seriously.

186
00:15:56,885 --> 00:15:59,185
Dad, it's me, Bang Geul.

187
00:16:03,855 --> 00:16:07,125
Please wake up. You're really starting to worry me.

188
00:16:09,725 --> 00:16:11,535
Dad, I'm here.

189
00:16:11,695 --> 00:16:16,665
When Director Song's car exploded, it was insane.

190
00:16:18,335 --> 00:16:19,405
I'm here.

191
00:16:20,905 --> 00:16:24,175
"Give me a call." "You have to report to the Governor anyway."

192
00:16:25,345 --> 00:16:27,345
He was putting on such an act.

193
00:16:27,885 --> 00:16:30,385
But I guess taking charge of the Governor's aide...

194
00:16:30,445 --> 00:16:31,855
and even Kang Jae Gyeong...

195
00:16:32,085 --> 00:16:33,555
is pretty impressive.

196
00:16:36,885 --> 00:16:39,095
I'm going to be the head of the Strategy and Planning Team.

197
00:16:39,855 --> 00:16:41,425
Until you get back,

198
00:16:41,965 --> 00:16:43,165
I'll protect Choiseong.

199
00:16:44,195 --> 00:16:47,164
Dad. I got one over on my sister.

200
00:16:47,165 --> 00:16:49,465
If you had seen it, you'd have told me I did a good job.

201
00:16:50,335 --> 00:16:52,775
So please hurry and wake up!

202
00:16:53,035 --> 00:16:55,345
When you wake up, I'll introduce you to Hwang Jun Hyeon.

203
00:16:55,705 --> 00:16:57,145
I bet you'll like him. Just like I do.

204
00:16:58,575 --> 00:16:59,575
No.

205
00:17:00,315 --> 00:17:01,685
I don't mean "like" in that way.

206
00:17:02,385 --> 00:17:05,915
No... But it's not like that's not true either.

207
00:17:08,185 --> 00:17:09,285
I don't know.

208
00:17:11,225 --> 00:17:13,195
I don't know!

209
00:17:28,705 --> 00:17:29,845
Thank you so much...

210
00:17:30,145 --> 00:17:32,075
for coming back, Hwang Jun Hyeon.

211
00:17:34,915 --> 00:17:36,985
I'm thankful too, Ms. Bang Geul.

212
00:17:39,315 --> 00:17:40,915
Did you get hit on the head?

213
00:17:42,285 --> 00:17:45,255
Where did they hit you? Here? Or here?

214
00:17:45,525 --> 00:17:47,495
Chairman Na... I swear I won't let him get away with this.

215
00:17:48,025 --> 00:17:49,195
First, let's get you to a hospital.

216
00:17:49,795 --> 00:17:52,235
I'm really okay.

217
00:17:53,165 --> 00:17:56,035
- I'm perfectly fine. - What do you mean you're fine?

218
00:17:56,205 --> 00:17:58,905
You've never been this nice to me before.

219
00:17:59,205 --> 00:18:01,805
I really don't feel a thing.

220
00:18:04,375 --> 00:18:06,745
What? What is it?

221
00:18:07,945 --> 00:18:09,215
Should we just head inside for now?

222
00:18:09,445 --> 00:18:13,655
Are you seriously craving bone broth soup in your condition?

223
00:18:15,755 --> 00:18:16,755
I'm sorry.

224
00:18:20,395 --> 00:18:23,165
You're right. A proper meal is where we get our strength.

225
00:18:25,465 --> 00:18:27,965
Ladies first? What do you know about manners?

226
00:18:28,305 --> 00:18:29,305
You're hurt.

227
00:18:29,365 --> 00:18:30,905
We're going straight to the hospital after we eat.

228
00:18:31,635 --> 00:18:32,635
Okay.

229
00:18:38,015 --> 00:18:39,175
Someone is in there.

230
00:18:40,775 --> 00:18:41,785
Should I go in?

231
00:18:46,955 --> 00:18:48,025
Hello.

232
00:19:08,175 --> 00:19:09,605
I'll get it.

233
00:19:17,845 --> 00:19:20,155
Just do something.

234
00:19:21,055 --> 00:19:24,255
How can a smart chairman like you not know? Good luck.

235
00:19:24,325 --> 00:19:26,855
- Enjoy your meal. - Hey, you little punk...

236
00:19:33,165 --> 00:19:34,295
Sit down.

237
00:19:48,315 --> 00:19:49,515
What happened?

238
00:19:50,985 --> 00:19:53,255
Jae Seong and Seok Do...

239
00:19:54,685 --> 00:19:56,554
They thought that if they somehow saved me...

240
00:19:56,555 --> 00:19:58,455
after I suddenly started breathing again,

241
00:19:59,095 --> 00:20:03,925
everything would go back to normal.

242
00:20:07,965 --> 00:20:10,235
As for that guy, Hwang Jun Hyeon...

243
00:20:10,635 --> 00:20:13,775
He just happened to run into me, and...

244
00:20:15,975 --> 00:20:17,045
Anyway,

245
00:20:19,275 --> 00:20:20,815
I'm just glad nothing happened to you.

246
00:20:24,855 --> 00:20:26,685
To protect a good-for-nothing father like me...

247
00:20:26,755 --> 00:20:27,955
who's done so little for you,

248
00:20:28,955 --> 00:20:30,455
you went through so much trouble.

249
00:20:31,125 --> 00:20:32,125
I know.

250
00:20:33,525 --> 00:20:35,664
I don't know why I bothered. It's not like I expected a thank you.

251
00:20:35,665 --> 00:20:38,995
What? No, that's not what I meant...

252
00:20:49,405 --> 00:20:50,445
Are you okay?

253
00:21:09,325 --> 00:21:10,365
I...

254
00:21:11,895 --> 00:21:16,105
never thought I'd see you again like this. I really didn't.

255
00:21:21,705 --> 00:21:23,045
I was afraid it was all my fault.

256
00:21:24,305 --> 00:21:27,445
That what happened to you was because I resented you.

257
00:21:28,085 --> 00:21:30,415
You have no idea how much I blamed myself.

258
00:21:30,815 --> 00:21:32,185
I was worried it was all my fault.

259
00:21:39,355 --> 00:21:42,665
Do you know why I named you Bang Geul?

260
00:21:45,135 --> 00:21:46,895
You didn't even cry when you were born.

261
00:21:47,535 --> 00:21:49,665
You'd just beam at me whenever we made eye contact.

262
00:21:50,535 --> 00:21:52,135
You were always smiling.

263
00:21:56,005 --> 00:21:58,875
My goodness, look at you crying now.

264
00:22:00,815 --> 00:22:01,845
Let me.

265
00:22:03,015 --> 00:22:04,015
Okay.

266
00:22:05,115 --> 00:22:06,455
You were always good at doing things on your own.

267
00:22:07,055 --> 00:22:08,455
Always so strong and capable.

268
00:22:11,185 --> 00:22:13,395
Still, what kind of name is Bang Geul?

269
00:22:13,725 --> 00:22:15,525
It makes me sound like an orphan you just found somewhere.

270
00:22:16,725 --> 00:22:17,795
Found you? Don't be ridiculous.

271
00:22:18,335 --> 00:22:19,765
You're my flesh and blood.

272
00:22:19,965 --> 00:22:22,235
Jenny, Jae Yeon, or Jae A.

273
00:22:22,405 --> 00:22:23,905
There are so many prettier names.

274
00:22:25,835 --> 00:22:26,905
Dad.

275
00:22:28,445 --> 00:22:30,705
But this is real, right?

276
00:22:32,415 --> 00:22:34,615
You're not going to disappear again, right?

277
00:22:36,915 --> 00:22:37,915
No.

278
00:22:53,595 --> 00:22:55,405
Why's he so awkward?

279
00:22:56,205 --> 00:22:57,905
He should just pull her in for a hug.

280
00:23:17,485 --> 00:23:22,325
Oh, my boy. Are you okay? Let me see you.

281
00:23:22,525 --> 00:23:25,235
Oh, my goodness. Did you not get hurt?

282
00:23:25,465 --> 00:23:27,065
My goodness, I can't believe it.

283
00:23:28,165 --> 00:23:29,165
Grandma.

284
00:23:33,475 --> 00:23:34,735
Have you been well?

285
00:23:36,005 --> 00:23:37,005
Of course.

286
00:23:37,345 --> 00:23:41,245
I've been living in such luxury, I'm practically going stir-crazy.

287
00:23:42,515 --> 00:23:43,515
Let's go inside.

288
00:23:48,355 --> 00:23:51,555
I've been taking them well, since you nagged me about it so much.

289
00:23:52,825 --> 00:23:54,655
I'm like Ronaldo.

290
00:23:56,695 --> 00:24:00,395
It does all the cleaning, and that one does the dishes.

291
00:24:00,765 --> 00:24:02,305
This one does all the laundry.

292
00:24:02,835 --> 00:24:06,005
My goodness, you won't let me lift a finger,

293
00:24:06,305 --> 00:24:08,305
so Grandma's been bored lately.

294
00:24:08,545 --> 00:24:12,075
How did you recognise me? I wasn't even in my uniform.

295
00:24:12,715 --> 00:24:15,145
We spend so much time together,

296
00:24:15,185 --> 00:24:17,185
I can tell it's you just from your footsteps.

297
00:24:17,615 --> 00:24:19,655
I'll think, "Oh, my boy is home from work."

298
00:24:19,985 --> 00:24:23,725
Or, "Looks like he had a good day today." I can tell everything.

299
00:24:25,755 --> 00:24:28,095
I should've just stayed with you.

300
00:24:28,495 --> 00:24:32,595
- I'm sorry, Grandma. - No. Let's eat, my boy. Come on.

301
00:24:32,665 --> 00:24:35,635
- Grandma. - Oh, yes, my boy.

302
00:24:49,785 --> 00:24:50,915
Who are you?

303
00:24:53,715 --> 00:24:55,884
- Have you been well, - Have you been well,

304
00:24:55,885 --> 00:24:57,285
- handsome mister? - handsome mister?

305
00:24:57,725 --> 00:24:59,025
Oh, Jun Hyeon.

306
00:24:59,925 --> 00:25:01,925
I was so worried.

307
00:25:03,125 --> 00:25:04,295
Hey, you went through a lot.

308
00:25:06,195 --> 00:25:07,365
Thank you.

309
00:25:08,835 --> 00:25:09,905
You went through a lot.

310
00:25:11,565 --> 00:25:13,075
You met your dad?

311
00:25:13,705 --> 00:25:15,575
I thought I was dreaming,

312
00:25:16,075 --> 00:25:17,845
but Dad was right there in front of me.

313
00:25:20,015 --> 00:25:22,245
I really thought it was a dream.

314
00:25:24,115 --> 00:25:25,655
But then I heard his voice.

315
00:25:29,585 --> 00:25:31,025
It was really him.

316
00:25:34,625 --> 00:25:35,865
Thank you.

317
00:25:37,495 --> 00:25:39,465
Thank you so much.

318
00:25:45,675 --> 00:25:47,705
Let's get all dressed up...

319
00:25:48,875 --> 00:25:50,945
and go see Dad, Ms. Jo Seon Hee.

320
00:25:59,985 --> 00:26:03,585
Thank you so much for taking care of my grandma, Manager Park Bong Gi.

321
00:26:03,755 --> 00:26:05,925
Is he crazy? What's wrong with him?

322
00:26:08,055 --> 00:26:11,425
They say a near-death experience changes a person.

323
00:26:12,695 --> 00:26:14,365
He keeps calling me "Ms. Bang Geul"...

324
00:26:14,435 --> 00:26:16,265
and being so formal. It's really weird.

325
00:26:16,605 --> 00:26:18,605
I'm really okay, Bang Geul.

326
00:26:21,905 --> 00:26:23,574
What's with your face? Why are you so warm?

327
00:26:23,575 --> 00:26:25,445
- It's creepy. - What?

328
00:26:26,875 --> 00:26:30,585
What kind of person did you make me out to be, Chairman Kang?

329
00:26:31,285 --> 00:26:33,815
I met with Kang Jae Gyeong.

330
00:26:35,425 --> 00:26:37,855
I even declared that I'd take over Choiseong Group.

331
00:26:38,085 --> 00:26:42,825
- Did Kang Jae Gyeong let you go? - Well, about that...

332
00:26:42,925 --> 00:26:45,135
Kang Jae Gyeong must be having a mental breakdown right now.

333
00:26:45,995 --> 00:26:48,765
- She was shocked to see my dad. - See your dad?

334
00:26:49,265 --> 00:26:52,005
What, did she see Chairman Kang's ghost or something?

335
00:26:53,235 --> 00:26:54,235
Not his ghost.

336
00:26:54,905 --> 00:26:55,905
The real him.

337
00:26:56,345 --> 00:26:59,115
- What? - My dad is alive, Manager Park.

338
00:26:59,945 --> 00:27:01,645
Oh, what nonsense.

339
00:27:04,345 --> 00:27:05,755
Hey, now...

340
00:27:09,285 --> 00:27:11,754
- Gosh... - Manager Park!

341
00:27:11,755 --> 00:27:13,525
- Manager Park, are you okay? - Manager Park.

342
00:27:16,895 --> 00:27:19,535
Please get some rest. I'll go get Mom.

343
00:27:47,955 --> 00:27:52,165
(To Father)

344
00:27:59,605 --> 00:28:02,205
Father, it's me, Jae Seong.

345
00:28:04,605 --> 00:28:06,775
I still don't have the courage to face you,

346
00:28:06,875 --> 00:28:10,245
so please forgive this undutiful son for writing a letter instead.

347
00:28:13,385 --> 00:28:16,225
A man with no ability went crazy for the chairman's seat,

348
00:28:17,625 --> 00:28:20,095
and it feels like I'm the one who drove you to this point.

349
00:28:25,235 --> 00:28:27,665
If only I had apologised to Hwang Jun Hyeon back then...

350
00:28:29,365 --> 00:28:31,605
and was properly punished for the hit-and-run,

351
00:28:32,605 --> 00:28:35,745
you wouldn't have had to go through such terrible things.

352
00:28:37,005 --> 00:28:40,045
I'm filled with immense regret every single day.

353
00:28:43,115 --> 00:28:44,985
For my son's sake,

354
00:28:45,755 --> 00:28:47,855
I will no longer be a father he is ashamed of.

355
00:28:49,055 --> 00:28:50,055
As for Jae Gyeong,

356
00:28:50,825 --> 00:28:52,725
I've made the preparations...

357
00:28:53,055 --> 00:28:54,455
so that you can be the one to finish things.

358
00:28:58,265 --> 00:28:59,565
Until we meet again,

359
00:29:01,095 --> 00:29:02,365
please stay healthy.

360
00:29:04,565 --> 00:29:07,235
Your eldest son, Kang Jae Seong.

361
00:29:15,885 --> 00:29:17,245
My son...

362
00:29:20,215 --> 00:29:22,185
has finally grown a conscience.

363
00:29:39,035 --> 00:29:40,775
Was this house always this big?

364
00:29:43,275 --> 00:29:44,505
Welcome home, Chairwoman.

365
00:29:46,875 --> 00:29:49,215
Why is it so quiet? Where's Kang Jae Seong?

366
00:29:49,385 --> 00:29:52,215
He said he found a house, so he left with I Jun.

367
00:29:52,785 --> 00:29:55,355
Il Jun went to Professor Min's family home.

368
00:29:56,085 --> 00:29:58,325
I see. What about Seok Do?

369
00:30:02,065 --> 00:30:03,395
Did you pull an all-nighter at the office?

370
00:30:03,965 --> 00:30:05,865
I just need to change and head right back out.

371
00:30:06,195 --> 00:30:07,565
You don't look well, honey.

372
00:30:08,095 --> 00:30:09,135
Have some breakfast before you go.

373
00:30:11,805 --> 00:30:12,905
(Secretary Yeo)

374
00:30:13,035 --> 00:30:14,035
Just a moment.

375
00:30:15,975 --> 00:30:16,975
Yes.

376
00:30:17,505 --> 00:30:18,505
Just listen.

377
00:30:19,475 --> 00:30:20,815
Your prediction was correct.

378
00:30:23,315 --> 00:30:25,655
Something felt off about him deleting all his GPS history,

379
00:30:25,985 --> 00:30:28,185
so I put a tracker on Professor Min's car.

380
00:30:29,785 --> 00:30:31,825
He's been regularly visiting a villa.

381
00:30:39,465 --> 00:30:41,665
This is the medication Professor Min took from the hospital.

382
00:30:42,105 --> 00:30:44,865
It's the same drug that was used in your father's treatment.

383
00:30:47,005 --> 00:30:48,975
My father's alive.

384
00:30:50,405 --> 00:30:52,645
Hwang Jun Hyeon and Kang Bang Geul must have known.

385
00:30:53,175 --> 00:30:55,545
Maybe even Jo Seon Hee and Lee Sang Jae, that whole crew.

386
00:30:55,915 --> 00:30:58,345
President Kang Jae Seong has called an emergency board meeting.

387
00:31:00,885 --> 00:31:02,125
To dismiss you as Chairwoman.

388
00:31:05,755 --> 00:31:07,625
Turns out I was the family outcast.

389
00:31:15,405 --> 00:31:18,505
This is your husband's car's last tracked location.

390
00:31:18,565 --> 00:31:19,805
(Crown Palace Hotel)

391
00:31:22,245 --> 00:31:23,245
What are you waiting for?

392
00:31:24,245 --> 00:31:26,175
My father has come back from the dead,

393
00:31:27,445 --> 00:31:29,945
and a good daughter should at least go see him.

394
00:31:50,305 --> 00:31:51,305
Yes.

395
00:32:05,885 --> 00:32:07,085
It really is you, Father.

396
00:32:11,225 --> 00:32:12,555
Why aren't you saying anything?

397
00:32:14,455 --> 00:32:15,895
Are you more surprised than I am?

398
00:32:17,865 --> 00:32:20,465
How do you manage to make me the villain every single time?

399
00:32:24,605 --> 00:32:25,775
About that day.

400
00:32:27,705 --> 00:32:30,545
The day you cut the strings on Jae Seong's harp.

401
00:32:38,615 --> 00:32:40,455
If I had scolded you then...

402
00:32:42,525 --> 00:32:44,355
No, that's not it.

403
00:32:45,395 --> 00:32:48,195
I was worried your pride, always being ahead of Jae Seong,

404
00:32:48,255 --> 00:32:49,395
would be your downfall.

405
00:32:50,665 --> 00:32:55,505
If I hadn't been a father so stingy with recognition and praise,

406
00:32:58,905 --> 00:33:01,205
we wouldn't have ended up like this.

407
00:33:04,975 --> 00:33:06,245
Why are you being like this all of a sudden?

408
00:33:16,925 --> 00:33:18,185
Because of my greed,

409
00:33:20,425 --> 00:33:23,225
I think I made you so lonely, Jae Gyeong.

410
00:33:33,435 --> 00:33:34,435
Let's...

411
00:33:35,645 --> 00:33:37,105
Let's go back together.

412
00:33:39,845 --> 00:33:41,345
It's not too late.

413
00:33:58,665 --> 00:33:59,665
No.

414
00:34:04,465 --> 00:34:05,835
It's far too late.

415
00:34:15,745 --> 00:34:17,485
If you're really sorry,

416
00:34:23,585 --> 00:34:25,855
then stay dead, Father.

417
00:34:53,055 --> 00:34:54,785
Until the emergency board meeting is over,

418
00:34:55,685 --> 00:34:57,155
hide him where no one can find him.

419
00:34:57,985 --> 00:34:58,995
Yes, Chairwoman.

420
00:35:05,665 --> 00:35:08,435
You can't take anything from me, Father.

421
00:35:17,605 --> 00:35:20,215
Where are you? Even if there isn't a warrant yet,

422
00:35:20,275 --> 00:35:21,375
this puts us in a difficult position.

423
00:35:21,815 --> 00:35:23,445
President Kang Jae Seong asked me to help you...

424
00:35:23,515 --> 00:35:25,785
- if you agree to turn yourself in. - Help me?

425
00:35:26,415 --> 00:35:28,555
Do you have any idea what I'm looking at right now?

426
00:35:28,715 --> 00:35:30,585
(Head of Choiseong's Legal Team)

427
00:35:34,295 --> 00:35:35,825
To frame me for murder,

428
00:35:38,195 --> 00:35:39,865
you took your own living father...

429
00:35:40,795 --> 00:35:42,605
and pretended he was dead, Kang Jae Gyeong?

430
00:35:55,445 --> 00:35:56,445
You're going to the emergency board meeting, right?

431
00:35:57,915 --> 00:36:01,885
Oh, yes. The emergency board meeting... Where was it?

432
00:36:01,955 --> 00:36:02,955
The main conference room, right?

433
00:36:03,225 --> 00:36:05,355
- This way. - You made it.

434
00:36:06,595 --> 00:36:07,595
That way.

435
00:36:10,525 --> 00:36:13,265
It's strange. Young Lady Bang Geul is really worried.

436
00:36:14,095 --> 00:36:15,095
I'm sorry.

437
00:36:16,935 --> 00:36:18,035
We're going to help you.

438
00:36:19,005 --> 00:36:21,735
Don't be nervous. Overwhelm them with your presence.

439
00:36:22,035 --> 00:36:23,045
Just like Chairman Kang.

440
00:36:26,475 --> 00:36:27,475
I know everything.

441
00:36:28,215 --> 00:36:30,815
What Chairman Kang and you went through, Hwang Jun Hyeon.

442
00:36:32,455 --> 00:36:34,515
Are you the Chairman's friend?

443
00:36:35,985 --> 00:36:37,025
I'm Lee Sang Jae.

444
00:36:37,985 --> 00:36:40,425
Thank you for holding on until the end.

445
00:36:42,155 --> 00:36:45,365
Now it's time for you to be rewarded for all you've been through.

446
00:36:50,705 --> 00:36:52,435
I'm sorry, I have to take this call.

447
00:36:53,305 --> 00:36:54,635
(Kang Smile)

448
00:36:55,375 --> 00:36:56,375
Yes, Ms. Bang Geul?

449
00:36:57,575 --> 00:36:59,245
Hwang Jun Hyeon, my dad's disappeared.

450
00:36:59,645 --> 00:37:00,845
He disappeared?

451
00:37:22,605 --> 00:37:24,935
The troublemaker himself hasn't even bothered to show up.

452
00:37:25,405 --> 00:37:27,905
That's typical of President Kang Jae Seong.

453
00:37:28,505 --> 00:37:30,775
I wonder when he'll ever grow up.

454
00:37:31,045 --> 00:37:34,475
- Unbelievable. - I planned to set something up.

455
00:37:34,775 --> 00:37:36,945
Please join me for dinner afterward.

456
00:37:37,715 --> 00:37:38,715
Yes.

457
00:37:39,155 --> 00:37:41,585
Everything is fine then, right?

458
00:37:41,985 --> 00:37:42,985
Of course.

459
00:38:02,705 --> 00:38:03,745
Hello.

460
00:38:04,305 --> 00:38:06,614
I'm Hwang Jun Hyeon. I stand before you today,

461
00:38:06,615 --> 00:38:08,545
vested with the authority of President Kang Jae Seong.

462
00:38:15,985 --> 00:38:17,185
I am proposing...

463
00:38:18,355 --> 00:38:19,625
Chairwoman Kang Jae Gyeong's dismissal.

464
00:38:21,795 --> 00:38:22,795
What is he talking about?

465
00:38:23,895 --> 00:38:25,565
Who does this guy think he is?

466
00:38:25,935 --> 00:38:28,795
After all the special treatment you received, you dare...

467
00:38:29,105 --> 00:38:32,634
- stab the Chairwoman in the back? - She's still having a hard time...

468
00:38:32,635 --> 00:38:34,405
coping with the late chairman's death.

469
00:38:34,675 --> 00:38:36,775
This is the problem with young people.

470
00:38:38,505 --> 00:38:39,915
Perhaps this is for the best.

471
00:38:40,275 --> 00:38:43,315
To stop any more of these unspeakable rumours from spreading,

472
00:38:44,285 --> 00:38:45,785
let's clear the air right here, right now.

473
00:38:46,585 --> 00:38:47,585
Right.

474
00:38:49,425 --> 00:38:50,955
You're shameless until the very end.

475
00:38:52,185 --> 00:38:55,025
Then let's talk about the sale of Choiseong C&T's hydrogen business.

476
00:38:55,295 --> 00:38:56,825
As I said,

477
00:38:57,225 --> 00:38:59,595
it was a contract forced upon us by Taeha Group's threats,

478
00:39:00,235 --> 00:39:02,065
and we're preparing a lawsuit to have it returned.

479
00:39:02,235 --> 00:39:05,165
And not to cut your ties with Chairman Na Byeong Mo?

480
00:39:10,345 --> 00:39:11,405
(Chairwoman Kang Jae Gyeong)

481
00:39:11,475 --> 00:39:12,974
This is an undisclosed agreement signed by...

482
00:39:12,975 --> 00:39:14,515
Chairwoman Kang Jae Gyeong and Chairman Na Byeong Mo.

483
00:39:14,675 --> 00:39:16,815
In addition to the disclosed sale price, 100 million dollars...

484
00:39:17,015 --> 00:39:18,745
and one percent of the hydrogen business's profit margin...

485
00:39:18,815 --> 00:39:20,685
would go to the private equity fund, Siren Capital Partners.

486
00:39:21,015 --> 00:39:22,085
That fund, Siren Capital Partners,

487
00:39:22,455 --> 00:39:25,125
is a major investor in Choiseong Chemical, as you all well know.

488
00:39:25,425 --> 00:39:28,295
Its true owner is none other than Catherine Kang,

489
00:39:29,265 --> 00:39:30,525
Chairwoman Kang Jae Gyeong.

490
00:39:39,375 --> 00:39:40,605
What are you talking about?

491
00:39:40,775 --> 00:39:43,205
Your money laundering buddies were quite resourceful, I hear.

492
00:39:44,745 --> 00:39:47,045
Selling off the evidence to double their profits.

493
00:39:49,415 --> 00:39:51,185
Have you hired the people for the laundry?

494
00:39:51,715 --> 00:39:53,885
The guys who helped you with Siren Capital Partners.

495
00:39:55,255 --> 00:39:56,955
For a long time, funds from Choiseong Chemical...

496
00:39:57,355 --> 00:39:58,355
were funnelled to Siren Capital Partners.

497
00:39:58,425 --> 00:39:59,555
We have evidence of that.

498
00:39:59,955 --> 00:40:01,955
- What? - My goodness.

499
00:40:04,125 --> 00:40:06,565
I would make a deal with the man who murdered my father?

500
00:40:06,935 --> 00:40:09,805
- That's ridiculous. - It's not so ridiculous.

501
00:40:11,865 --> 00:40:13,735
Not if she was a daughter who wanted her father dead.

502
00:40:15,805 --> 00:40:16,805
Are you crazy?

503
00:40:17,775 --> 00:40:19,175
How dare you say such a horrible thing...

504
00:40:21,345 --> 00:40:23,345
How long are you going to stand in my way?

505
00:40:24,945 --> 00:40:26,115
What are you still clinging to?

506
00:40:27,455 --> 00:40:28,655
Should I put an end to it for you?

507
00:40:34,455 --> 00:40:35,455
Oh, my goodness.

508
00:40:42,265 --> 00:40:45,505
They're trying to frame me as the killer.

509
00:40:45,765 --> 00:40:47,035
They're the ones who installed a camera...

510
00:40:47,105 --> 00:40:48,205
in my father's hospital room to spy on me.

511
00:40:48,775 --> 00:40:52,145
The ones who killed my father are Na Byeong Mo and Na Eun Se.

512
00:40:52,775 --> 00:40:54,415
If I were guilty, they would have arrested me.

513
00:40:56,215 --> 00:40:59,085
This is all a conspiracy to oust me from my position as chairwoman.

514
00:40:59,415 --> 00:41:00,715
You committed a hit-and-run with Kang Jae Seong...

515
00:41:00,785 --> 00:41:01,785
so you could become Chairwoman.

516
00:41:01,786 --> 00:41:04,355
Is framing your father for it also part of the conspiracy?

517
00:41:05,995 --> 00:41:07,855
Don't make baseless accusations.

518
00:41:08,725 --> 00:41:10,125
That's all in the past.

519
00:41:10,465 --> 00:41:11,965
President Kang Jae Seong has turned himself in.

520
00:41:13,865 --> 00:41:14,895
What?

521
00:41:16,035 --> 00:41:17,035
I stood by...

522
00:41:18,435 --> 00:41:19,904
and watched as Kang Jae Gyeong tried...

523
00:41:19,905 --> 00:41:21,775
to suffocate our father with a pillow.

524
00:41:22,275 --> 00:41:24,975
That's why our father fell into a coma.

525
00:41:25,545 --> 00:41:26,545
Why?

526
00:41:27,715 --> 00:41:29,315
To cover up the hit-and-run.

527
00:41:29,885 --> 00:41:30,915
She fabricated evidence...

528
00:41:30,985 --> 00:41:33,055
and even deceived the victim, Hwang Jun Hyeon.

529
00:41:33,515 --> 00:41:35,015
We pretended to offer compensation...

530
00:41:35,785 --> 00:41:37,755
and pushed him to hold a press conference.

531
00:41:38,285 --> 00:41:39,295
It was all...

532
00:41:40,395 --> 00:41:42,155
a scheme devised by Kang Jae Gyeong and me.

533
00:41:44,195 --> 00:41:46,235
You've all gone mad just to take me down.

534
00:41:51,465 --> 00:41:54,035
You should trust me. I built Choiseong into what it is today.

535
00:41:54,405 --> 00:41:56,005
I'm preparing to acquire Taeha Energy.

536
00:41:56,445 --> 00:41:57,675
In addition to the hydrogen business,

537
00:41:58,705 --> 00:42:01,545
our company, Choiseong, will dominate the global battery market.

538
00:42:01,645 --> 00:42:02,985
What is this about?

539
00:42:03,715 --> 00:42:04,715
This is...

540
00:42:05,115 --> 00:42:06,815
My father always dreamed of us being a top-five conglomerate,

541
00:42:06,885 --> 00:42:07,885
and we're so close.

542
00:42:07,955 --> 00:42:11,425
Are you just going to stand there and let these rumours ruin the group?

543
00:42:11,625 --> 00:42:13,055
No matter how I look at it,

544
00:42:18,425 --> 00:42:20,465
Kang Jae Gyeong, you're not fit to be the chairwoman.

545
00:42:23,105 --> 00:42:24,505
That's the message your father asked me...

546
00:42:26,475 --> 00:42:27,475
to deliver.

547
00:42:32,275 --> 00:42:33,575
Are you seeing ghosts?

548
00:42:34,745 --> 00:42:36,545
My father is dead. He can't talk.

549
00:42:36,845 --> 00:42:38,585
Who says I'm dead?

550
00:43:12,785 --> 00:43:13,785
Min Seok Do...

551
00:43:14,115 --> 00:43:15,985
I knew you were suspicious of me.

552
00:43:17,025 --> 00:43:19,255
I couldn't lose your father to you again.

553
00:44:03,805 --> 00:44:06,205
(Chairwoman Kang Jae Gyeong)

554
00:44:11,245 --> 00:44:12,575
It's time to stop...

555
00:44:14,575 --> 00:44:16,685
playing chairwoman, Jae Gyeong.

556
00:45:06,295 --> 00:45:07,735
It's not over yet.

557
00:45:09,865 --> 00:45:10,935
I said it's not over.

558
00:45:11,865 --> 00:45:12,935
It's not over.

559
00:45:20,045 --> 00:45:22,745
(Police)

560
00:45:46,435 --> 00:45:47,635
Jae Gyeong!

561
00:46:28,975 --> 00:46:30,585
- Dad! - Chairman!

562
00:46:31,815 --> 00:46:34,285
- Dad! - What do you think you're doing?

563
00:46:39,385 --> 00:46:40,555
Somebody help!

564
00:46:42,825 --> 00:46:44,695
(Police)

565
00:46:45,465 --> 00:46:46,835
Call an ambulance!

566
00:46:53,605 --> 00:46:54,735
Why did you do it?

567
00:46:57,445 --> 00:46:58,445
Why?

568
00:47:04,345 --> 00:47:06,215
Why on earth?

569
00:47:27,505 --> 00:47:34,245
(2 years later)

570
00:48:17,455 --> 00:48:19,055
She draws the same picture every time.

571
00:48:21,595 --> 00:48:22,995
She can't even remember her name.

572
00:48:23,065 --> 00:48:24,765
She's completely erased her own identity.

573
00:48:31,965 --> 00:48:33,335
Her denial is just too strong.

574
00:48:34,935 --> 00:48:36,745
She won't be able to forgive herself easily,

575
00:48:37,945 --> 00:48:38,975
for what she's done.

576
00:48:53,055 --> 00:48:54,655
Honey, I'm here.

577
00:49:00,565 --> 00:49:02,395
But still, you're the only one she remembers.

578
00:49:04,665 --> 00:49:05,835
The person she loves the most.

579
00:49:18,415 --> 00:49:20,055
- Come on. - Go.

580
00:49:20,455 --> 00:49:21,555
Nice.

581
00:49:23,985 --> 00:49:25,385
Aiden, Logan.

582
00:49:26,055 --> 00:49:28,525
It's been five hours already. Let's go home.

583
00:49:29,055 --> 00:49:30,095
Aren't you hungry?

584
00:49:32,265 --> 00:49:33,335
They're not even listening.

585
00:49:33,965 --> 00:49:36,735
Hey, how can you win all the time? You have to learn how to lose too.

586
00:49:36,805 --> 00:49:39,305
Me? I prefer losing.

587
00:49:42,105 --> 00:49:43,175
I'm really leaving.

588
00:49:43,775 --> 00:49:44,775
I'm going.

589
00:49:49,675 --> 00:49:50,985
Goodness.

590
00:49:53,015 --> 00:49:56,255
Yes. They're so competitive.

591
00:49:57,885 --> 00:50:00,895
They won't let their friends go home until they've won.

592
00:50:01,925 --> 00:50:04,095
I get such looks from the other parents. It's killing me.

593
00:50:04,465 --> 00:50:06,595
We're totally blacklisted.

594
00:50:08,165 --> 00:50:09,395
The apple doesn't fall far from the tree.

595
00:50:09,695 --> 00:50:11,804
Honestly, we weren't this bad.

596
00:50:11,805 --> 00:50:13,905
They're worse than Kang Jae Gyeong and I ever were.

597
00:50:17,705 --> 00:50:20,675
It's okay. We're a family.

598
00:50:22,515 --> 00:50:24,145
Il Jun... I mean,

599
00:50:25,685 --> 00:50:28,215
Logan will have to meet his mother someday too.

600
00:50:29,385 --> 00:50:30,385
Right?

601
00:50:31,285 --> 00:50:32,985
It'll just take a little more time.

602
00:50:33,325 --> 00:50:34,325
I was so worried...

603
00:50:34,395 --> 00:50:36,595
when you said you'd go with them to take care of the kids.

604
00:50:37,125 --> 00:50:39,695
But I'm relieved you're doing better than I expected, Jae Seong.

605
00:50:40,095 --> 00:50:41,335
It's a perfect fit for me.

606
00:50:41,895 --> 00:50:42,965
I feel at ease too.

607
00:50:43,265 --> 00:50:46,835
What about Korea? How could you not visit once in two years?

608
00:50:47,105 --> 00:50:49,235
I'll bring the kids over during their next school break.

609
00:50:49,735 --> 00:50:53,415
Actually, the kids are dying to have your food.

610
00:50:54,315 --> 00:50:56,215
Your view count exploded again, didn't it?

611
00:50:57,085 --> 00:50:58,085
You're a total superstar.

612
00:50:59,045 --> 00:51:01,055
Hi, my dear Chairmen.

613
00:51:01,355 --> 00:51:04,555
Hello. This is Jo from The Chairman's Table.

614
00:51:05,285 --> 00:51:09,355
Ta-da. I finally got my Gold Play Button.

615
00:51:09,525 --> 00:51:13,835
I dedicate it to one million Chairmen. Thank you.

616
00:51:15,835 --> 00:51:17,205
Today's dish is...

617
00:51:17,565 --> 00:51:19,165
shepherd's purse ramyeon.

618
00:51:24,345 --> 00:51:25,675
(The Chairman's Table)

619
00:51:28,445 --> 00:51:30,185
(Toycrane: Did you guys see the news about Choiseong Group?)

620
00:51:31,545 --> 00:51:32,785
What news?

621
00:51:34,815 --> 00:51:37,725
After a series of incidents, the founding Kang family...

622
00:51:37,985 --> 00:51:40,124
has completely stepped away from management.

623
00:51:40,125 --> 00:51:42,925
Now run by professionals, Choiseong Group...

624
00:51:42,995 --> 00:51:46,695
is showing remarkable growth, contrary to public concern.

625
00:51:46,935 --> 00:51:49,635
It is drawing up a new blueprint for Korea's conglomerate system,

626
00:51:49,765 --> 00:51:52,405
which has long been defined by hereditary succession.

627
00:51:52,705 --> 00:51:54,275
The growth of Choiseong C&T...

628
00:51:54,335 --> 00:51:56,644
is particularly remarkable. It is led by President Lee Sang Jae,

629
00:51:56,645 --> 00:51:58,205
who joined the group as a new employee,

630
00:51:58,475 --> 00:51:59,844
and later became an executive...

631
00:51:59,845 --> 00:52:03,285
and the managing director of the Strategy and Planning Team.

632
00:52:03,485 --> 00:52:06,755
Choiseong C&T also acquired Taeha Energy,

633
00:52:06,815 --> 00:52:08,155
the core business of the spun-off Taeha Group.

634
00:52:08,215 --> 00:52:10,154
It then launched Choiseong Rotem,

635
00:52:10,155 --> 00:52:12,855
becoming a leader in hydrogen mobility...

636
00:52:13,085 --> 00:52:15,055
Don't you have work to do?

637
00:52:15,525 --> 00:52:17,095
Did you come to work just to read that to me?

638
00:52:17,425 --> 00:52:19,525
Watch it. I'll have that Managing Director nameplate...

639
00:52:19,595 --> 00:52:20,595
taken off your desk.

640
00:52:20,665 --> 00:52:23,635
Do you think an executive director is the same as a department head?

641
00:52:23,935 --> 00:52:26,875
- What? - Managing Director Park Bong Gi...

642
00:52:27,275 --> 00:52:29,945
personally took charge and directed everything...

643
00:52:30,145 --> 00:52:33,045
to make sure it all runs like a well-oiled machine.

644
00:52:36,645 --> 00:52:37,785
I thought you were swamped with work.

645
00:52:38,145 --> 00:52:40,515
You kept begging me to hire some new people.

646
00:52:40,655 --> 00:52:44,185
Those new recruits are Team Leader Kang's responsibility.

647
00:52:44,925 --> 00:52:47,825
But I hear she's planning on cleaning house first.

648
00:52:48,355 --> 00:52:49,395
At Taeha Group.

649
00:52:50,625 --> 00:52:52,025
An investment firm from the Middle East...

650
00:52:52,795 --> 00:52:56,495
is interested in our dementia treatment patch, Altz-Seven.

651
00:52:57,235 --> 00:52:59,235
They're offering to invest 500 million dollars.

652
00:52:59,865 --> 00:53:01,305
So I told them we're currently in talks with Choiseong...

653
00:53:01,375 --> 00:53:03,575
- Is this a scam? - Pardon?

654
00:53:03,845 --> 00:53:06,405
The report said the natural drug compound is below the standard.

655
00:53:06,475 --> 00:53:07,475
If the FDA finds out,

656
00:53:07,545 --> 00:53:09,445
you know they'll issue a suspension of manufacturing, right?

657
00:53:09,715 --> 00:53:10,815
Oh, no, that's not right.

658
00:53:10,885 --> 00:53:13,485
We completed Phase Two trials without any issues.

659
00:53:13,585 --> 00:53:17,955
So you're saying the buyer can worry about Phase Three trials.

660
00:53:18,225 --> 00:53:20,825
And we just need to fudge the data and sell it for a high price,

661
00:53:20,895 --> 00:53:21,895
is that it?

662
00:53:22,555 --> 00:53:24,225
Are you trying to pull the wool over my eyes?

663
00:53:24,925 --> 00:53:27,095
Aren't you just trying to turn a profit from this M&A?

664
00:53:28,435 --> 00:53:30,535
Taeha was on the verge of being dismantled.

665
00:53:30,805 --> 00:53:32,304
But Choiseong took you in,

666
00:53:32,305 --> 00:53:34,375
guaranteeing job security for your employees.

667
00:53:35,305 --> 00:53:37,675
Let's not gamble with their livelihoods.

668
00:53:41,175 --> 00:53:43,275
All right. Goodbye.

669
00:53:47,285 --> 00:53:48,985
Right, new employee OJT.

670
00:53:56,795 --> 00:53:57,995
(Strategy and Planning Team)

671
00:53:59,965 --> 00:54:02,365
The Strategy and Planning Team is the core of Choiseong Group.

672
00:54:02,635 --> 00:54:05,865
It's produced many important people including me.

673
00:54:07,875 --> 00:54:11,345
When there's a project, collect your performance bonuses and incentives,

674
00:54:11,445 --> 00:54:14,175
don't let your bosses steal your ideas, look out for yourselves,

675
00:54:14,245 --> 00:54:17,315
and negotiate for a big raise. Understood?

676
00:54:18,815 --> 00:54:22,715
Then is that rumour true?

677
00:54:23,255 --> 00:54:25,125
What rumour would that be?

678
00:54:28,425 --> 00:54:30,794
That the Choiseong owners distributed their shares...

679
00:54:30,795 --> 00:54:32,564
to employees as bonuses based on performance,

680
00:54:32,565 --> 00:54:34,565
and donated the rest to society?

681
00:54:35,195 --> 00:54:36,195
That one?

682
00:54:39,335 --> 00:54:41,005
There's one last place I want to show you.

683
00:54:53,855 --> 00:54:56,155
(Anyone at Choiseong has the right to become Chairman.)

684
00:54:56,285 --> 00:54:57,285
It's true.

685
00:54:58,555 --> 00:54:59,985
A company where the employees are the owners.

686
00:55:01,095 --> 00:55:02,925
A place where you earn what you're worth.

687
00:55:03,625 --> 00:55:06,195
The lifelong career you've only heard about in stories.

688
00:55:08,565 --> 00:55:10,405
If you want it, Choiseong will make it happen.

689
00:55:11,035 --> 00:55:13,205
That doesn't apply to new hires like us.

690
00:55:13,675 --> 00:55:14,675
That's not true.

691
00:55:15,735 --> 00:55:16,745
There was one.

692
00:55:17,445 --> 00:55:21,115
A legendary rookie who almost became the Chairman of Choiseong Group.

693
00:55:24,315 --> 00:55:26,545
(Anyone at Choiseong has the right to become Chairman.)

694
00:55:29,255 --> 00:55:30,425
Pass it through!

695
00:55:36,225 --> 00:55:37,225
Pass!

696
00:55:38,225 --> 00:55:40,095
Shoot! Out!

697
00:55:40,665 --> 00:55:43,435
Good try. Stay focused. Don't get down!

698
00:55:43,765 --> 00:55:45,805
Okay, pass it to Yong Seong.

699
00:55:46,305 --> 00:55:47,775
Good, Yong Seong, shoot!

700
00:55:48,475 --> 00:55:49,475
Goal!

701
00:56:28,615 --> 00:56:32,485
- Hello, Mr. Chairman! - Hello, Mr. Chairman!

702
00:56:32,545 --> 00:56:36,515
Hey, guys. Gosh, Yong Seong, great shot.

703
00:56:36,755 --> 00:56:39,425
Seo Jun, that was a killer pass.

704
00:56:39,725 --> 00:56:41,825
I've booked the rib place just up ahead,

705
00:56:42,095 --> 00:56:45,695
so go eat till you burst. Five servings each.

706
00:56:48,635 --> 00:56:51,564
Keep working hard just like your coach.

707
00:56:51,565 --> 00:56:52,565
- Yes, sir. - Yes, sir.

708
00:56:52,605 --> 00:56:53,605
Go on.

709
00:56:55,875 --> 00:56:56,875
You're here.

710
00:56:59,275 --> 00:57:01,745
What in the world are you wearing?

711
00:57:03,145 --> 00:57:04,585
You think you look any better, Chairman?

712
00:57:05,045 --> 00:57:06,245
What's this, the "young at 70" look?

713
00:57:10,285 --> 00:57:11,285
Let's go.

714
00:57:12,685 --> 00:57:14,955
You're going to Hae Chan's send-off next month, right?

715
00:57:15,255 --> 00:57:18,695
Of course. He's our first player to make it to the EPL.

716
00:57:19,725 --> 00:57:23,065
He's our golden goose. He's going to make our team a prestigious club.

717
00:57:23,195 --> 00:57:25,134
I knew he was special from the moment I saw him.

718
00:57:25,135 --> 00:57:27,175
His thighs are huge. Solid as a rock.

719
00:57:27,405 --> 00:57:29,805
I'm the one who recommended him for his killer shot with both feet.

720
00:57:29,905 --> 00:57:32,175
Never let me have the last word, do you? All right, you're the big shot.

721
00:57:32,245 --> 00:57:33,745
How'd you know? You've been checking?

722
00:57:35,215 --> 00:57:39,015
And since you're seeing Ok Sun after so long, try to smile, will you?

723
00:57:39,085 --> 00:57:41,415
No. Your grandma doesn't like me.

724
00:57:41,685 --> 00:57:43,385
I acted like her grandson and guardian.

725
00:57:43,455 --> 00:57:45,525
I took such good care of her when you were away.

726
00:57:45,755 --> 00:57:47,295
My grandma likes you, Chairman.

727
00:57:47,355 --> 00:57:49,295
She said she'd love for us to become family.

728
00:57:49,395 --> 00:57:51,925
She made a whole feast and is waiting for us right now.

729
00:57:52,225 --> 00:57:53,225
Become family?

730
00:57:53,835 --> 00:57:54,835
Who?

731
00:57:59,265 --> 00:58:01,805
Aren't I supposed to be meeting your girlfriend today?

732
00:58:02,905 --> 00:58:04,875
- Right. - Right.

733
00:58:05,345 --> 00:58:08,315
Right, so about that.

734
00:58:10,245 --> 00:58:11,245
Just a second.

735
00:58:13,445 --> 00:58:17,525
- I told you not to come get me. - What?

736
00:58:18,585 --> 00:58:21,125
I'm just going to grab my bag,

737
00:58:21,455 --> 00:58:23,455
so don't do anything. Just stay right here. Okay?

738
00:58:26,795 --> 00:58:28,265
That little brat...

739
00:58:30,935 --> 00:58:32,165
It can't be.

740
00:58:32,305 --> 00:58:33,905
The poster photoshoot...

741
00:58:33,935 --> 00:58:35,675
for the movie "Mafia" will begin shortly.

742
00:58:35,735 --> 00:58:39,775
All relevant staff, please gather at the front of the east-side seating.

743
00:58:41,715 --> 00:58:45,185
Why isn't Bang Geul answering her phone?

744
00:58:46,445 --> 00:58:47,455
No way...

745
00:58:48,415 --> 00:58:50,155
No, it couldn't be. Surely not.

746
00:58:51,325 --> 00:58:52,685
My daughter is way out of his league.

747
00:58:53,255 --> 00:58:54,855
How can he even be compared to the ace of Choiseong Group?

748
00:58:55,225 --> 00:58:57,495
I have to nip this in the bud. This can't happen.

749
00:59:20,955 --> 00:59:22,385
Busted!

750
00:59:23,925 --> 00:59:25,785
Men and women should keep proper boundaries.

751
00:59:29,155 --> 00:59:30,565
In broad daylight?

752
00:59:31,195 --> 00:59:32,965
Have you no sense of shame?

753
00:59:37,165 --> 00:59:38,665
- Hello. - Let's give it our all.

754
00:59:38,735 --> 00:59:40,605
Chairman, it's not what it looks like.

755
00:59:40,675 --> 00:59:44,045
- What do you think you're doing? - Dad, please, just calm down.

756
00:59:55,655 --> 00:59:57,925
- Oh, my back. - Dad, are you okay?

757
00:59:59,755 --> 01:00:01,255
Chairman, are you okay?

758
01:00:01,695 --> 01:00:02,695
Darn it.

759
01:00:02,825 --> 01:00:05,094
I told you this new prosthetic leg would take time to get used to,

760
01:00:05,095 --> 01:00:06,595
and that you should be careful.

761
01:00:07,435 --> 01:00:08,865
And who might you be?

762
01:00:11,105 --> 01:00:13,205
Do you know my dad?

763
01:00:36,295 --> 01:00:37,495
This is driving me crazy.

764
01:00:38,425 --> 01:00:41,195
This can't be real. This just can't be, right?

765
01:00:41,265 --> 01:00:42,335
What's going on?

766
01:00:42,395 --> 01:00:46,335
No, why? What is this? Why am I here?

767
01:00:48,335 --> 01:00:49,505
Oh, my. This...

768
01:00:50,605 --> 01:00:51,605
Hey.

769
01:00:52,345 --> 01:00:53,875
Is it a mask?

770
01:00:54,645 --> 01:00:58,685
It's so detailed. Are we twins, by any chance?

771
01:00:58,985 --> 01:01:00,715
A Doppelganger or something?

772
01:01:04,155 --> 01:01:05,525
Doppelganger.

773
01:01:06,325 --> 01:01:07,525
Doppelganger.

774
01:01:08,025 --> 01:01:12,025
Doppelganger. What? What's wrong with my voice?

775
01:01:17,265 --> 01:01:19,005
(We wish Choiseong FC the best of luck.)

776
01:01:24,545 --> 01:01:25,605
(We wish Choiseong FC the best of luck.)

777
01:01:37,385 --> 01:01:39,285
What did you do to me?

778
01:01:40,495 --> 01:01:41,495
Well...

779
01:01:42,595 --> 01:01:44,595
- Let me explain what happened. - Are you okay?

780
01:01:44,665 --> 01:01:46,625
- Are you okay? - Ryujin, we have to go now.

781
01:01:46,695 --> 01:01:48,965
Are you okay? There's no time. I'm sorry, but we're out of time.

782
01:01:49,035 --> 01:01:50,635
Wait a minute.

783
01:01:52,135 --> 01:01:55,175
- I'm not her. - I'm the real one, right?

784
01:01:55,675 --> 01:01:56,675
Look.

785
01:01:58,505 --> 01:02:02,975
- See? It's me. - That one's the real one.

786
01:02:03,445 --> 01:02:04,445
That one's the real one.

787
01:02:05,315 --> 01:02:08,055
"Stop nagging." This is me. This one.

788
01:02:08,115 --> 01:02:09,855
- Yes, we saw. Hurry up, let's go. - I'm sorry. Let's go.

789
01:02:09,915 --> 01:02:11,825
- Let's go. - Thank you.

790
01:02:13,355 --> 01:02:14,355
Why...

791
01:02:15,125 --> 01:02:17,025
I'm telling you, it's me!

792
01:02:19,765 --> 01:02:21,135
It's me!

793
01:02:29,575 --> 01:02:32,575
(Reborn Rookie)

794
01:02:53,795 --> 01:02:55,795
(Special thanks to Ryujin for her guest appearance)

795
01:02:55,895 --> 01:02:57,165
Between the corporate affiliates...

796
01:02:58,465 --> 01:03:00,335
- I'm sorry. - How dare you!

797
01:03:00,835 --> 01:03:02,005
Let's go for one more take.

798
01:03:03,005 --> 01:03:05,145
How do I do it? How am I supposed to...

799
01:03:09,375 --> 01:03:10,445
It's pretty.

800
01:03:11,515 --> 01:03:12,615
- What? - Go.

801
01:03:12,685 --> 01:03:13,685
"It's pretty."

802
01:03:14,785 --> 01:03:16,155
Kwang Bang Geul is...

803
01:03:16,855 --> 01:03:17,885
Kwang Bang Geul?

804
01:03:19,885 --> 01:03:21,825
Thanks to you, mother and daughter are about to cough up everything,

805
01:03:21,895 --> 01:03:23,625
including the penalty for the slush fund.

806
01:03:23,695 --> 01:03:25,365
- I'm so sorry. - Why?

807
01:03:25,465 --> 01:03:26,695
I just hope...

808
01:03:29,735 --> 01:03:30,865
you'll be happy.

809
01:03:31,405 --> 01:03:32,405
Thank you.

810
01:03:33,265 --> 01:03:35,005
This mood isn't great.

811
01:03:35,675 --> 01:03:37,175
- All because of a little prank. - What...

812
01:03:39,475 --> 01:03:42,345
- Yes, okay, that's good. - Let's do it.

813
01:03:44,115 --> 01:03:46,215
We've been on good terms until now, Manager Park, right?

814
01:03:46,285 --> 01:03:47,915
You jerk!

815
01:03:48,215 --> 01:03:49,215
What do I do?

816
01:03:50,385 --> 01:03:53,785
What did you do to me? Who's laughing? Stop laughing.

817
01:03:54,155 --> 01:03:55,755
I'm sincerely grateful.

818
01:03:56,355 --> 01:03:57,365
I love you all.

819
01:03:58,365 --> 01:04:01,695
Lee Jun Young, thank you for your hard work these five months.

820
01:04:02,035 --> 01:04:04,335
We love you. Last bust shot.
